\title{Sign of Permutation}
\taxon{Definition}
\import{macros}
\p{
    The \strong{sign} of a [permutation](def-003Y) #{\sigma\in S_n} is a function #{\sgn:S_n\to\{-1,1\}} defined as
    #{\sgn(\sigma) = 1} if #{\sigma} requires an even number of permutations and 
    #{\sgn(\sigma) = -1} if #{\sigma} requires an odd number of permutations to get the identity permutation.
}